The paper discusses a theory and database related to DNA promoter sequences, which involves testing systems that integrate empirical and analytical learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions an exhaustive search of the space of M-of-N domain theory interpretations, which suggests that it may be relevant to the database systems (cs.DB) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) sub-categories.
